<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DCM AND DDM DRUM TYPE PARKING BRAKE - BENDIX DUO DUTY MECHANICAL BRAKE - REMOVAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0402112">Figure 12</hotlnk>for all Item numbers in parentheses.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0402112" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g0402112" filename="../figg04/G0402112.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                     scalefitheight="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. DDM Brake Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CABLE MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CLEVIS PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>3. CLEVIS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. COTTER PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LOCKNUT</callout1>
                <callout1>6. BRAKE CABLE CLAMP</callout1>
                <callout1>7. BRAKE CABLE</callout1>
                <callout1>8. BRAKE DRUM</callout1>
                <callout1>9. COMPANION FLANGE</callout1>
                <callout1>10. DDM BRAKE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>11. CAMSHAFT BALL</callout1>
                <callout1>12. BEARING RETAINER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block wheels to prevent vehicle from moving.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the universal joint trunnion bolts and lower the drive shaft to the floor. Refer to
                GROUP 06 - PROPELLER SHAFT in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for service information for the type of
                shaft being disconnected.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bolts holding trunnion and drum to the companion flange.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove companion flange (Item 9) from the main shaft.The flange is normally splined to the
                shaft and is secured with a castellated nut and cotter pin.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the brake assembly (Item 10) from its mounting flange.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
